 Management Team – Nohla Therapeutics



























































 

 














 




Management Team

Nohla’s Management Team collectively has decades of experience in corporate development and financing, clinically relevant stem/progenitor cell expansion, hematology/oncology, cGMP manufacturing, process development and scale-up.










Benjamin Bergo Chief Executive Officer
Ben is the CEO of Nohla Therapeutics where he has played a pivotal role in leading the business strategy, corporate transactions and building the executive team. Prior to this role he was the Executive Chairman of Cytomatrix Limited, a company engaged in early stage stem cell expansion research. Ben previously co-founded and served as Managing Director of a privately financed diagnostics company with technology in-licensed from Harvard University. Ben worked for close to five years in venture capital where he held executive roles in portfolio companies and prior served in operating roles at Vision Systems Limited until its acquisition by Danaher Corporation in 2006.











Dr. Colleen Delaney Chief Medical Officer
Colleen is the Chief Medical Officer at Nohla Therapeutics. She is also an Associate Member and recipient of the Madeline Dabney Adams Endowed Chair of the Fred Hutch Clinical Research Division and an Associate Professor at the UW Department of Pediatrics, Division of Pediatric Hematology/Oncology. Dr. Delaney is a member on the Advisory Council on Blood Stem Cell Transplantation of the Health Resources and Services Administration. She also serves on the Boards of Directors of the American Society of Bone Marrow Transplant and the Cord Blood Association.
In 2006, she established and became the Director of the Cord Blood Transplant Program at the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center/Seattle Cancer Care Alliance, which has grown to be one of the busiest such programs in the country and the coordinating center of several multicenter clinical trials. She is the sponsor-investigator of three Investigational New Drug FDA files and has been the Principal Investigator of nine ongoing and completed clinical trials and several ancillary studies.
Dr. Delaney is also the Principal Investigator of a research laboratory focused on the role of the Notch signaling pathway in hematopoietic stem cell regulation and ex-vivo expansion of umbilical cord blood stem and progenitor cells for clinical applications. Her group at Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center developed novel and clinically feasible methods for the ex vivo expansion of cord blood derived hematopoietic stem and progenitor cells in the presence of Notch ligands. This work was translated into a pilot study investigating the use of ex vivo expanded cord blood progenitors to augment conventional cord blood transplantation. She has since extended this work to investigate the potential of cryopreserved, non-HLA matched “off the shelf” ex vivo expanded cord blood progenitor cells to provide rapid but transient myeloid reconstitution in the setting of cord blood transplant and following dose-intensive chemotherapy.
Dr. Colleen Delaney received her MD from Harvard Medical School in 1996, and went on to complete a residency in Pediatrics at the University of California, San Francisco followed by a Fellowship in Pediatric Hematology/Oncology at Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center/University of Washington.











Dr. Mark Kirkland Chief Scientific Officer
Mark is a Hematologist and stem cell researcher with a wide and varied experience in tissue banking, cGMP, commercial biotechnology and both public and private pathology. Mark served as Chief Science Officer at Cytomatrix, working on developing  various scalable solutions to stem cell expansion. His previous roles have included Chief of Service of Geelong Hospital Pathology Service, Chairman of PathCare Consulting Pathologists, Regional Transfusion Officer and Director of Research for Australian Red Cross Blood Service, and Chief Scientific Officer for Cygenics Ltd.











Michael Sistenich Chief Business Officer
Michael is the Head of Corporate Development and responsible for capital raising and major corporate transactions for Nohla Therapeutics. He previously worked as Head of Corporate Development at Cytomatrix, and  led the life sciences investment banking practice at Bell Potter Securities, leading over A$100mn placements through the past year. Prior to that he held the role of Head of Healthcare Investments at DWS Investments of Deutsche Bank in Europe, and has over 18 years of experience as a healthcare specialist in international investment management and investment banking.











Jason Carstens Vice President of Manufacturing
Jason Carstens is our Vice President of Manufacturing and is responsible for process development, quality systems, and manufacturing operations at Nohla Therapeutics. Previously he held the position of Staff Scientist and Director, Process Development and Manufacturing at the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center where he supported the development and manufacture of numerous stem cell and T-cell therapeutic products. Prior to that Jason was the Director of Process Development at CMC Biologics, a contract manufacturing organization, where he was involved in the development, scale-up, and commercialization of more than 40 different biological drug products. He is also active in mentoring undergraduate and graduate students and holds an appointment at the University of Washington as an Affiliate Assistant Professor in the Department of Chemical Engineering.
Jason earned a PhD from the University of California, Berkeley and a BS from the University of Washington, both in the field of Chemical Engineering.











Darren Scotti Chief Financial Officer
Darren is a CPA with over 20 years experience specialising in business expansion, financial modeling and negotiating Darren has honed his skills in a wide range of industries and diverse businesses from large multi-nationals to small to medium owner-operator concerns. Darren’s expertise is in wholesale, distribution and supply chain gained through his role as CFO with Michelin Australia and The Heat Group (a combined 10 years), an insolvency specialist with Coopers and Lybrand and in an investment review role with 3i, the UK’s largest venture capitalist.











Claudia Gregorio-King Clinical Operations Manager
Claudia Gregorio-King has a PhD in cord blood biology, and has spent the last 10 years working in the biotechnology field, including 4 years in Clinical Research Organisations as Senior Project Manager. She has taken up the position of Clinical Projects Manager and will be planning and implementing clinical trials.











Heather Brammer Director of Program Management
Heather has 20 years of experience encompassing a broad range of biotechnology expertise from discovery research through GMP scale-up of biologics, devices, and cell therapies, to BLA approval and commercialization. Before joining Nohla Therapeutics, Heather served as Program Manager for the CB Transplant Program at Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center under Dr. Colleen Delaney, coordinating development and manufacturing projects and clinical trials related to expanded stem cells derived from cord blood. She was also part of a cross-functional team working on public outreach and education of the life-saving potential and outcomes of cord blood transplants.
She initially started out at the Hutch in 2010 managing the Quality Assurance oversight of the GMP cell processing facility. Prior to that she spent six years at ZymoGenetics first as a Quality Control scientist and then as Quality Assurance Manager of Commercial Products, establishing the medical device program and eventually participating in the BLA approval and launch of  Recothrom® and Recothrom® Spray Kit.
She started out her biotech career with an internship at ICOS corp. while working on her Anthropology degree from University of Washington. She then moved into a research position in a leukocyte biology lab, screening macrophage libraries and developing functional assays and characterization methods of purified proteins.











Guy Moeneclaey Research Manager
Guy Moeneclaey is the Research Manager for Nohla Therapeutics. Guy has worked for many years in biotechnology, and specifically haematopoiesis, most recently as Senior Manager of Clinical Research with Miltenyi Biotech in Europe. He brings a wealth of experience to the position and will play a critical role in progressing the core expansion technologies, managing our research institute partners and interface into product development.





































Benjamin Bergo | Nohla Therapeutics Inc | Email CEO @nohlatherapeutics.com CFO 

















































